Grammar of Láadan

VERB ORDER

TENSE - PERSON/HON = NUMBER - ATTRIB - ASPECT - root - GENDER - COMP = NEG - HABIT - EVID

Tense prefixes (originally independent):

aril- = future (dialectal aríli)
é- = past (eril)
Ø- = present (ril)
rilrili- = subjunctive
wi = optative (wil)

Person/honorific prefixes (originally independent):
l(e) = 1sg
n(e) = 2sg
b(e) = 3sg
behid = 3sg masc
behig = 3sg fem
b(e) = 3sg plur
-i = deferential
-a = intimate
lhe- = formal

 — note that when the subject is masculine, there is indeed double marking.

Number prefixes:

-Ø- = singular
-g-/-ge- = paucal
-n-/-me- = plural (originally -n on subject and me- prefix)

Attributive prefix:

wo-

Aspect prefixes:

du- = conative
ná- = continuative
raa- = "again" (ne-)
elith- = cessative (no-)

Gender suffix:

-id = masc.

Complementizer suffix:

-hé (dial. -hée)

Negative suffix:

-ra

Habitual suffix:

-badan (dial. bradan, bada, bradá, brada)

Evidentiality suffixes:

-álh  = perceived (wa)
-wi = self-evident
-yen = dreamt (we)
-athá = of trustworthy source (wáa)
-waálh = of untrustworthy source

Degree suffixes:

-úulhik = slightly
-ulh = minor
-hal = very
-háalik = extremely

these are comparative/superlative and reverse comparative/superlative.

Emphatic suffix:

-hóo

------------------------------------------------------------

Bíide eríli thi Doni daneth nede neda, i ndi with woho beth wáa.

becomes

e-thi-athá Doni dan-th nedeneda i n-di-athá with woho beth